14:
Chest of Relics, I call on thee!
Armaments one thru six, furnish
unto me!
16: Meet your glorious end! Relic Ruina—
32:
I've TOLD you why. Don't bring out
the big guns for the small-fry!
36:
If the hunter is not careful, he may
be outsmarted by the hare.
42:
I feel like this is more a case of the
elephant being afraid of the mouse.
45:
Just last night, you were talking
about how you didn't want to go
within ten feet of a monster.
50:
What's said in the shadows must
stay in the shadows!
53:
T-think of me as a long-range
fighter! The Chest of Relics draws its
inspiration from none other than the
arms of the royal family.
56:
As long as I wield it, even that
useless prince poses no—
62:
Why'd you ask me for training then?
In case you haven't noticed, I fight
with my claws.
65:
Looks like they want to rumble. Show
me what you've got, Libram. You
and ONE sword.
73:
Well, well... If it isn't Libro. Shoulda
recognized that screaming. Looks
like you made some rad friends.
85:
So, like, this happened right after
we'd bombed a quest. We were
there, drinking away our sorrow,
when this dude comes strolling up.
86:
And you know how it always sounds
like he's talking down to you? So we
were about to take him out back
when he starts bawling like a baby.
91:
That's what we thought at first, but
then we totally bonded over our
problems. So now, when we're in the
mood for a rant, we go drinking
together.
93:
We grab him when we need a
wingman too. Hate to admit it, but
Libro's face can draw a crowd.
94: Bout the only thing he CAN do.
99:
Is the last thing... *pant* I am to
hear... *wheeze* before my death...
*pant* this SLANDER?!
102:
But he gives you hope, you know?
Always says, "If all it takes is a bit of
steel to turn a reed like me into a
champion, imagine what you can
become."
104:
I mean, I don't want to rely on no
weapons but... Libro tries, you know?
122:
...They truly meant to abandon me
to my fate. The fiends!
124:
Hah... Hahaha... But now, I have been
awakened to my true power. Soon,
even that little prince will bow—
134:
I bear a message from the House of
Swes.
141:
He's been like that ever since we got
home. The hell happened?
146:
Something big, probably. Look, he
hasn't touched his honey omelet!
152:
Haha. Maybe wittle baby Wibram
wants us to spoon-feed him.
Choo-choo.
162:
All jokes aside, let us know if
whatever's bothering you gets to be
too much, okay? We're here to help.
166:
I have things under control for now.
But... I desire a second plate of this
honey omelet.
175:
Tell my brother this: I cannot and will
not accept his terms.
177:
Do you mean to betray your own
house?
179:
Swes is a house of merchants. It is
our duty to engage in trade that will
bolster the livelihood of our kingdom.
180:
In trade, all parties must stand to
gain. If so much as a single party is
harmed, then it is violence.
182:
Who then, do you think, is the one
bringing shame upon our family?
190: What do you mean by this?
197: This is the calm... before the storm...
204:
What was their aim? To...
assassinate me?
206:
Brother... Have you at last decided to
clasp the blood-stained hand of
Kwetur?
